	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100805973962404><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Most important advice to a newbie</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=124073><span id= >AeroBLASTER</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>95 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 11th 3:35 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is the most important advice you will hear about starting up your druid.<br><br>PUT EVERY SINGLE POINT IN TO WISDOM.<br><br>Wisdom dictates how much mana you will have.&nbsp;&nbsp;Without mana, you will die.  Period.  While at first you can do ok meleeing, as you rise in levels, it will become clear that you are as mana dependant as any other spellcasting class.  If you are early in levels (below 20) and did not put all your points into Wisdom, then start over.  Good luck!<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
